title: Lesson 1: Introduction
description: All about you and the app

elements.name: promoter_features
elements.title: Intro
elements.description: Welcome to Lattitude Career Companion, your holistic navigator through the complex voyage of professional and personal growth.

elements.name: question3
elements.title: Why this app is so important:

elements.html: Mentors are the compasses that guide us through career development but can be tricky to find.

elements.name: question7
elements.html: Lattitude can equip you with the skills and best practices of how to find them, what to ask them and how to make the most of your time together.

elements.name: question10
elements.html: You’ll likely need several diverse mentors, individuals with varied experiences and perspectives.

elements.name: question12
elements.html: Just as organizations rely on a board of directors for governance and a board of advisors for expertise and advice, Lattitude uses the concept of a "Personal Board of Advisors" (PBA), a curated team of mentors, enthusiasts, and specialists committed to your growth and success.

elements.name: question14
elements.html: Harvard Business Review, Fortune, MIT Sloan Management Review, CNBC, Napoleon Hill and others underscore the importance of a personal advisory board.

elements.name: question4
elements.title: What you can do on the app:

elements.name: question18
elements.html: • Identify your life’s purpose or “Ikigai” and define a personal point of success.

elements.name: question19
elements.html: • Grow and curate your Personal Board of Advisors (PBA).

elements.name: question21
elements.html: • Develop your Career Map and consult your PBA along the way.

elements.name: question25
elements.html:
“Absorb what is useful, discard what is not, and add what is uniquely your own.”
- Bruce Lee

elements.name: Tips on how to get the most from Lattitude Career Companion:
question6
elements.html:
• The app alone cannot guarantee your success. Only what you take from it and apply can accomplish that.
  • Actively apply the outlined principles and strategies.
  • Professional growth is a marathon, not a sprint, which will require focused effort and a commitment to applying what you learn.
  • Cultivating a “growth mindset” is key to prepare for a transformative experience.
  • Take action by integrating the concepts with real-life practices, setting clear goals, and maintaining a journal for reflections and insights.
  • Set clear intentions and goals. What specific goals or aspirations do you have for building a PBA? Write them down and keep them in mind as you progress through each lesson.
  • Take notes, journal, and self reflect.
  • Seek support and accountability by connecting with peers on similar paths.

elements.name: question26
elements.html: Let's set sail together, leveraging the right mix of technology and human wisdom, with Career Companion guiding you toward realizing your professional goals and potential. This isn’t just a journey; it’s an expedition towards achieving a fulfilling career and personal growth, with your PBA by your side every step of the way.
